Wants a Divorce.

Suit for divorce has been commenced by Martha C. Hansen against her husband Gabriel. They were married May 5, 1876, at Clinton, Iowa. Mrs. Hansen alleges that her husband has treated her brutally for the past ten years, while their children are kept at hard work and depreved of school privileges, one of them, a very diminutive girl, being kept pickign up coal along the railroad track to furnish the fuel for the family.
